      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "To maximize your efficiency score, replace the Python loop with a single vectorized operation using NumPy, which processes the entire data stream in compiled C code instead of interpreted steps.\nYou should also move the threshold check to aNumPy array and apply a sliding window or batching strategy to reduce memory allocation overhead per entry.\nFinally, ensure that error handling is minimized to prevent runtime exceptions from adding overhead, as errors kill your latency metrics immediately.\n\n```python\nimport numpy as np\n\ndef process_sensor_data(data_stream):\n    data = np.array([e['value'] for e in data_stream])\n    mask = data > 0.5\n    transformed = np.where(mask, (data[mask] * 1.5) / (data[mask] + 0.1), 0.0)\n    return list(transformed)\n```",
